Semantic Web Homework 1 – Recipe Recommendation System

Team: Dan Maria-Andrada (frontend + backend), Grec Carina-Gabriela (XML, XSD, XPath + backend)
Github link: https://github.com/carina-grec/recommend-recipes-hw1-semantic-web.git

Description:
This project is a Java web application built with Spring Boot that recommends recipes to users based on their cooking skill level and preferred cuisine type.

Technologies Used:
- Java (Spring Boot)
- XML (data storage)
- XML Schema (XSD) for validation
- XPath for querying XML data
- XSL for transforming XML into HTML
- Thymeleaf (UI)

Main Features:
1. Recipes are stored in an XML file and validated using XSD.
2. Recipes can be scraped from BBC Good Food (titles only).
3. Users can add new recipes and users via forms.
4. Recipes are recommended based on:
   - cooking skill level
   - cooking skill level + preferred cuisine
5. Recipes can be filtered by cuisine type.
6. Recipe details can be viewed individually.
7. Recipes are also displayed using XSL transformation with:
   - yellow highlight for matching skill
   - green for non-matching recipes
8. User selection is available for recommendations (UI improvement).

How to Run:
1. Open the project in an IDE - IntelliJ
2. Run the main class: RecommendRecipes.java
3. Open browser at: http://localhost:8080



